SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1124
By Hensley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Breonna Lashay Grinder,
2026 Top Ten Senior of Lewis County High
School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Breonna Lashay Grinder is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named a Top Ten Senior of the 2026 graduating class at Lewis County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Grinder has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Breonna Grinder has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including serving as Sergeant-In-Arms for Beta Club and the Newsletter, Book, and Writing Club
and as secretary for Pilot Club; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Grinder has received many awards and accolades, including the Beta
Club Award, the TCAT Presidential Honors Award, and the Most Positive Student Award; she
has also received awards for having the highest average in multiple subjects, including Spanish,
art, government and civics, world history, biology, and English; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Grinder's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for her future success as a student at Middle Tennessee State University, where she plans to
study animation; and
SJR1124
017659
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Breonna Grinder's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride
for her parents, Brian Grinder and Shay Grinder, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Grinder's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor Breonna Lashay
Grinder on being named a 2026 Lewis County High School Top Ten Senior, salute her
impressive academic achievement, and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful
future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
